rmk: I saw three of these migrant Asian Brown Flycatchers in conflict in the early morning. I first heard the birds making loud calls. They were located 3-5 meters apart on high trees. Intermittently one would chase the other off the perch. They exhibited aggressive physical conflict with beaking. The conflict I observed lasted from 7.30-7.50am and continued even after I moved on. Wells (2007) notes that “freshly arrived stagers and winterers interact aggressively, with much chasing an vocalising until they settle into exclusive spaces ..”.
